					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The SNES already has top of the line looking games, Star Ocean for example, using the extra power for more graphics fidelity is a moot point. Using it to improve physics and AI would be handy though. Also using it to do on the fly decode of graphics so you can do smaller loads from the Disc and pack more into RAM would probably be useful. <br /><br />The other thing is the C lamers can probably just code in C on the new chip and avoid having to do ASM. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_razz.gif" alt=":P" title="Razz" /><br /><br />I also think if we can get the CD-ROM system working with say more RAM, that it would be a lot cheaper and easier to sell and market new games on CDs rather than expensive repro carts, or repro carts with expensive custom chips like CICs and MSUs</div>

